				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Battle of Wits: Poisoner&#039;s Dilemma" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Poisoner's Dilemma is a quick micro-game containing only four cards. The cards come in a custom printed sleeve that holds the whole game. &amp;#10;The game is inspired by the scene in &amp;quot;The Princess Bride&amp;quot; where Vizzini and Westley face off in a Battle of Wits.&amp;#10;Westley serves two goblets of wine for the two to drink. But one goblet is tainted with poison! Which one??? &amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;It ends when you decide and we drink &amp;#10;and find out who is right and who is dead.&amp;rdquo; -Westley&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of three cards: two wine cards and one poison card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Entire Rules of Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each person starts with 3 life. &amp;#10;The first person to zero life is dead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Choose one person to be the Dealer and the other to be the Player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Round Description:&amp;#10;1. The Dealer chooses one card to remove from &amp;#10;the game for the round.&amp;#10;2. The Dealer serves one face-down card to the Player &amp;#10;and one to themselves.&amp;#10;3. The Player chooses whether to drink the from card in front of themselves or from the card in front of the Dealer. &amp;#10;The Dealer drinks from the other card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a. If the poison card is in the game, whoever drinks it loses 1 life.&amp;#10;b. If the poison card is not in the game and the Player chooses their own card, no one loses a life.&amp;#10;c. If the poison card is not in the game and the Player chooses the card in front of the Dealer, it is a grave insult to the Dealer&amp;rsquo;s integrity, and the Dealer punches the Player. The Player loses a life.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Switch the role of Player and Dealer for the next round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
